claimAll(uint256[],bytes32[],uint256).details: Claims user's tokens from a single round

claimSingle(uint256,uint256[],bytes32[],.details: Claims user's tokens from a single round

returns._0: Claimed claimed amount for user in round

params.rounds_: array of unlock schedule for each round

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

resetROOT(bytes32,string).details: function to reset ROOT if allocations changed

params.leaves_: is new link to allocations information
params.root_: is new merkle tree root hash

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unlocked(uint256,uint256).details: Calculates unclaimed total amount of tokens

returns._0: amount Amount of tokens that are free to be claimed

withdraw(address,uint256).details: function to claim all left tokens (only owner)
